cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CE 

This paper deals with detecting falsified sensor measurements in a system, which falls under the category of system and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses simulations of a chemical reactor, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CR). The paper proposes a model-based approach, which involves using dynamic detectors and leveraging the history of the state, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with identifying attacks on sensors, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
